            . I am a <rs id="t18221023-40-viclabel219" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-40-victim459 t18221023-40-viclabel219"></join> woman, and keep a house in <placeName id="t18221023-40-crimeloc220">Union-street, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18221023-40-crimeloc220" type="placeName" value="Union-street, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18221023-40-crimeloc220" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-40-off217 t18221023-40-crimeloc220"></join>. The prisoner lodged eight months with me; he went away last Friday week, and said he was going into Greenwich-Hospital. Last Tuesday night I went out a little before eight<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182210230030"></xptr>o'clock, and returned a little past eleven o'clock, I missed my things; I had fastened the front door, the back door was just shut.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221023-40-person463">
                  HANNAH 
                  SIMPSON
               <interp inst="t18221023-40-person463" type="surname" value="SIMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-person463" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-person463" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I went out with Tuffnell. The things hung on the line, some of them were mine; when I returned they were gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221023-40-person464">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18221023-40-person464" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-person464" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-person464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of Shadwell. About eleven o'clock last Tuesday night, I stopped the prisoner on my beat, with a bundle under his arm, coming in a direction from the prosecutrix's house; he said they were his clean things, that he was going on board his ship; he had two goblets under his jacket, which made me suspect him. He struggled, but I secured him, and in the watch-house he said he got them from the prosecutrixes.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They took all my money, and promised to keep me till I got a ship; she kicked me out of doors. I did not intend to make away with the things.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 36.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18221023-40-verdict221" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-verdict221" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-verdict221" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               stealing only
            </rs>. - <rs id="t18221023-40-punish222" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18221023-40-punish222" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-40-defend457 t18221023-40-punish222"></join>
               Confined One Month
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Second Middlesex Jury, before Mr. Justice Park.</p>
